:::summary
Agriculture — the deliberate cultivation of crops and domestication of animals for food, fiber, and other products — is the foundational technology of human civilization. Without it, no city, no empire, no library, and no cathedral could have been built. The Bible is saturated with agricultural imagery, from the Garden of Eden to the parables of Jesus, and the Christian tradition has long understood farming as a participation in God's ongoing care for creation. The Latter-day Saint tradition, with its strong heritage of pioneer settlement and the principles of the Word of Wisdom, gives agriculture a distinctive spiritual dimension.
